{
  "texts": [
    "For all cases, the single-task DPA-2 models are exclusively trained on the datasets specified in the second column, whereas the multi-task DPA-2 model undergoes pre-training on the entire corpus of pre-training datasets (see Table 1).",
    "The multi-task DPA-2 model then employs the fitting head indicated in the second column to initialize the fitting procedure for downstream tasks.",
    "All model variants are evaluated on their respective downstream datasets without any additional training.",
    "The results demonstrate that multi-task training substantially enhances generalizability compared to the single-task pre-trained DPA-2 and the MPtrjtrained models.",
    "The comparable performance between the MPtrj-trained MACE-MP-0 and DPA-2 suggests that the improvement is primarily due to the multi-task pre-training scheme rather than differences in model architecture."
  ]
}